qtuneSimple[source]

qtuneSimple(params, evaluate, n_pop=10, cxpb=0.6, mutpb=0.6, ngen=10, hof=2, elitism=True, stats=<deap.tools.support.Statistics object at 0x7fefd176ccf8>, crossover=cxDictUniform, select=selTournament, mutate=mutDictRand, n_jobs=1, seed=None, verbose=True)

Quick tune using eaSimpleWithExtraLog. Just provide parameter list and function to tune. The function given should accept keywords arguments in the parameter list. Check examples below for more information.

{% endraw %} {% raw %}
{% endraw %}

Example of using qtuneSimple

{% raw %} 
from eptune.parameter import *
params = [
    FloatParameter([-100, 200], 'x'),
    FloatParameter([-100, 200], 'y')
]


def evaluate(params):
    return [params['x']**2+params['y']**2]
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
%%time
popu, logbook, hof = qtuneSimple(params,evaluate,cxpb=0.6,
                            n_pop=30, mutpb=0.6,
                            ngen=500, elitism=False,
                            seed=42, verbose=False)
fig = logbook.plot(['min','avg'])
